    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/7–2848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jessup</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-30T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 30, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>493. Dept concurs in views expressed <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 963
                    July 28 except for para 9 as to which no opinion is expressed at this time.</p>
                <p>Dept has following additional comments: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Dept underscores your para 1 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) and (<hi
                                rend="italic">b</hi>). We are now hopeful of change in US Displaced
                            Persons Act during special session to <pb facs="0755" n="1263"
                                xml:id="pg_1263"/> eliminate discrimination against Jewish <gloss
                                target="#t_DP1">DP</gloss>s. Two bills already introduced in each
                            House Congress to this effect. Proposed UK action might be seriously
                            prejudicial.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Security Council consideration of general refugee–displaced persons
                            problem would give Soviet and Ukrainian delegations excellent
                            opportunity not previously presented Security Council to exploit this
                            subject and should be avoided if at all possible.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>As to alternatives in your para 8 Dept strongly prefers (<hi
                                rend="italic">b</hi>) with understanding that such approach made
                            without prejudice to Mediator’s freedom of action to take such other
                            measures as he deems desirable. Dept also underscores reasons expressed
                            your para 2 (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>). Course proposed para 8 (<hi
                                rend="italic">c</hi>) also should be pursued. Depts Advisory
                            Committee Vol Foreign Aid already negotiating with appropriate US
                            organizations but viewed realistically it appears that no prospects of
                            large scale relief exist. Alternative (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) would
                            be preferable to Security Council action but should not be undertaken
                            unless alternative (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) proves unfeasible.<note
                                n="1" xml:id="d500fn1">This telegram was repeated to London as
                                3015.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
